  "text": "Mean age was 45.8 years (range 22-83 years). Median duration of monitoring was 66.5 h (range 48-130 h). Patient diagnosis included IIH (7), Chiari malformation (type 1) (3), secondary hydrocephalus (2), congenital hydrocephalus (2), ventriculomegally (2), chronic headaches (1) and iNPH [CITATION_1] . No infections or other complications were observed following ICP monitoring. ",
